aladins using 1h weapons, I'd be greatful.<br><br><br>Kaejz<br>55 Dark Elven Mymirdon<br><br>Saenen<br>24 Half Elven Paladin <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/umoonshaetheknight.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Moonshae the Knight</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 21<br> <font color=#333333>(5/26/01 7:49:04 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fthecrossroadstavern8833frm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.carolina.rr.com/sfod/images/moonshae_sm.jpg height=132 width=160></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What Weapons for a Paladin?</span><hr size=1> I use a one hand weapon and shield, mainly because of the bash to interrupt spellcasters.  At level 30 with stun and bash you will be able to interrupt most spells if you time it right, which when you're fighting healers is a great advantage.  In my opinion a paladin isn't there to deal the most damage, we're there to take it and prevent it being done to others.  So the extra ac and abilities some shields offer is also important.<br><br>If you are not the primary tank and/or not fighting a caster, then a two handed weapon is a good option if you want to deal more damage.  I usually carry both on me, but I prefer to use the one handed with shield in most circumstances. <p><table cellspacing="2" cellpadding="10" border="1" bordercolor="#4169E1" bgcolor="black" align="center"><tr><td align="center"><font color="#E9E9E9" face="arial" size="4"><b>Moonshae Silverwind</b><br></font><font color="#4169E1" face="arial" size="3"><b>- 50th Knight of Tunare -</b><br></font></td></tr></table></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/ubromsots.showPublicProfile?